  "text": "As for ensemble models (RF and GBDT), the training procedure follows the traditional QSAR pipeline. [CITATION_1] A particular model is then trained to predict the corresponding toxicity endpoint. Note that except for specifically mentioned, all our results shown in following tables are the average outputs of 50 numerical experiments. Similarly, to eliminate randomness in neural network training, we build 50 models for each set of parameters and then use their average output as our final prediction.",
